        <h2>About Our Cafe</h2>
        <p>Suraphat's Cafe is a cozy place to relax and enjoy a variety of premium coffee, teas, and freshly baked goods. Located in the heart of the city, our cafe offers a serene atmosphere with modern decor and exceptional customer service. Whether you're looking for a quiet corner to work or a place to catch up with friends, Suraphat's Cafe is your perfect destination.</p>

        <div class="history">
            <h2>Our History</h2>
            <p>Suraphat's Cafe was founded in 2020 by สุรพัต อาจต้น, a coffee enthusiast with a vision to create a space where people could connect, relax, and enjoy premium beverages and delicious food. Starting as a small neighborhood cafe, it quickly gained popularity due to its dedication to quality and customer satisfaction.</p>

            <p>Over the years, Suraphat's Cafe has expanded to include more seating options, a beautiful outdoor garden, and even a workshop space for events. Our mission has always been to provide not just great coffee, but a memorable experience for everyone who walks through our doors.</p>

            <h3>Milestones:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>2020:</strong> Cafe grand opening with a team of three passionate baristas.</li>
                <li><strong>2021:</strong> Launched our first monthly coffee brewing workshop.</li>
                <li><strong>2022:</strong> Expanded our menu to include healthy options and artisanal teas.</li>
                <li><strong>2023:</strong> Recognized as the Best Community Cafe in the city by the Local Business Awards.</li>
            </ul>

            <p>Today, Suraphat's Cafe continues to thrive as a beloved gathering spot for locals and tourists alike. We are committed to innovation and excellence in everything we do, from crafting the perfect cup of coffee to creating a warm and welcoming environment.</p>
        </div>

        <h3>Our Offerings:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Specialty Coffee: From classic espresso to unique latte art creations.</li>
